HEADWORD: Symploce
<hw>Sym"plo*ce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/ an interweaving, fr. <?/ to twine together; <?/ + <?/ to
twine.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>The repetition of a word or phrase
at the beginning and another at the end of successive clauses; as,
<xex>Justice</xex> came down from heaven to view <xex>the earth</xex>;
<xex>Justice</xex> returned to heaven, and left <xex>the
earth</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

